<chapter id="interface">
<title>User interface</title>
<para>This section describes the interface of <application>cssed</application>. For description of plugins interface, see <xref linkend="Plugins">.</para>

<sect1 id="interface-description">
<title>Description</title>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-cssed-ui-small">
<title id="figure-cssed-ui-small-title"><application>cssed</application> user interface</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/cssed-ui-small" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/cssed-ui-small.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The <application>cssed</application> UI</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>The <application>cssed</application> user interface is divided into three main sections:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>The menu and tool bars: give quick access to the <application>cssed</application> main functions.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>The editor notebook: is located in the upper right corner of <application>cssed</application> interface and contains all editor windows.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>The side panel: Located on the right side of <application>cssed</application> interface, it comprises two tabs. The first one contains the selector scanner and the <acronym>CSS</acronym> property's tree view, the second one contains the digest.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>The program output, the scratch pad/static pad, and optionally the terminal: are in the footer of <application>cssed</application> interface.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>Additionally, you will find tips just by pausing the mouse over most elements of the interface, and contextual menus are available in the document window and in the scratch pad/static pad.</para>
</sect1>

<sect1 id="interface-menu">
<title>The menu and tool bars</title>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-menutoolbars">
<title id="figure-menutoolbars-title">Menu and tool bars</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/menutoolbars" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/menutoolbars.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The <application>cssed</application> menu and tooI bars</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>The menu and tool bars are common to other editors. From the menu, you can perform most <application>cssed</application> tasks; you will use the tool bars to perform the most common ones. All menus have got menu accelerator keys, but not all items in menus.</para>
<note><para>Mac OS X users: the menu accelerator keys are not available on your system. </para></note>
<para>Here we will inspect the menus, and let you know the possible equivalence in the tool bars.</para>

<sect2 id="interface-file-menu">
<title>The File menu</title>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-filemenu">
<title id="figure-filemenu-title">File menu</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/filemenu" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/filemenu.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The File menu</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>This is where you perform actions on files:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>New, Open</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Close, Close all</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Revert</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Save, Save as, Save all</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Quit</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<tip><para>Those actions, but Close all, Revert, Save all, and Quit, are accessible from the first part of the main tool bar.</para></tip>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-maintoolbar1">
<title id="figure-maintoolbar1-title">Equivalence of the File menu in the main tool bar</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar1" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar1.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>New, Open, Save, Save as, Close from the main tool bar</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<note><para>Notice that the Close action applies to the current document.</para>
<para>Notice also the accelerator keys for most common actions in this menu.</para></note>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="interface-edit-menu">
<title>The Edit menu</title>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-editmenu">
<title id="figure-editmenu-title">Edit menu</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/editmenu" format="EPS">
</imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/editmenu.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The Edit menu</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>This is where you perform actions on documents:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>Undo and Redo</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Cut, Copy, Paste and Delete</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Find, Find and Replace</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>In addition, this is where you access <application>cssed</application> preferences.</para>
<tip><para>Those actions, but Delete, are accessible from the 2nd, 3rd, 4th and last part of the main tool bar.</para></tip>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-maintoolbar2-4">
<title id="figure-maintoolbar2-4-title">Equivalence of the first part of the Edit menu in the main tool bar</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar2-4" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar2-4.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Cut, copy, paste, find, find and replace, undo and redo from the main tool bar</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>
<figure float="0" id="figure-maintoolbar7">
<title id="figure-maintoolbar7-title">Equivalence of the last part of the Edit menu in the main tool bar</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar7" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/maintoolbar7.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Preferences from the main tool bar</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<note><para>Once again, notice the accelerator keys for most actions in the Edit menu. Notice that <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>Z</keycap></keycombo> for undo works, though not signaled in the menu.</para></note>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="interface-view-menu">
<title>The View menu</title>
<para><figure float="0" id="figure-viewmenu">
<title id="figure-viewmenu-title">View menu</title>
<screenshot><mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/viewmenu" format="EPS"></imageobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/viewmenu.png" format="PNG"></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The View menu</phrase></textobject>
</mediaobject></screenshot>
</figure></para>
<para>This is where you can change the visual display of the <application>cssed</application> window.</para>
<para>From here you can:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>Hide / Show the main and secondary tool bars</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Change the zoom factor of the current document</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Create, modify and load documents lists which will ease grouping and opening documents</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>Those actions have no equivalence in the tool bars.</para>
</sect2>

